Create a new skill: obs-claude/skills/k8s-health-check/SKILL.md                                                                   
                                                                                                                                    
  Purpose: Read-only health check for any Kubernetes cluster — nodes,                                                               
  workloads, and events. Works with any kubeconfig, no repo required.                                                               
                                                                                                                                    
  Arguments:                                                                                                                        
    --kubeconfig <path>   required                                                                                                  
    --namespaces <ns,...> optional, default: all non-system                                                                         
    --verbose             optional, show pod-level detail                                                                           
    --output <path>       optional, write report to file                                                                            
                                                                                                                                    
  What it checks (in order):                                                                                                        
    1. Nodes — Ready/NotReady, CPU/memory pressure, cordoned                                                                        
    2. Deployments/StatefulSets — not ready, unavailable replicas                                                                   
    3. Pods — CrashLoopBackOff, OOMKilled, Pending, ImagePullBackOff                                                                
    4. PVCs — Pending/Lost                                                                                                          
    5. Warning events — last 1h, deduplicated                                                                                       
    6. Resource pressure — top nodes if metrics-server available
    7. Check vmagent namespace.
    8. Also check if there are any pending messages on the queue.
    9. Check the pods using excessive pods and report them
    10. Provide a summary in text format on command prompt and generate a CSV file with full details and store it in output file.                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
  Output:                                                                                                                           
    - Traffic-light summary table per namespace (GREEN/AMBER/RED)                                                                   
    - Drill-down detail for any RED/AMBER namespace                                                                                 
    - Clean namespaces listed briefly at the bottom                                                                                 
    - Optional file report to $HOME/outputs/                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                    
  Constraints:                                                                                                                      
    - Read-only always, no remediation                                                                                              
    - Production and non-prod both allowed (read-only)                                                                              
    - Use parallel agents for scanning when > 10 namespaces                                                                         
    - No --repo dependency, no Helm required                                                                                        
    - Follow skill header/footer format from                                                                                        
      $HOME/.claude/reference/skill-post-run-report.md                           
